On%20those%20days%2C%20when%20my%20teen%20daughter%20tries%20to%20talk%2C%20one%20of%20us%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteenage-daughters-healthy-relationship-communication-snacks-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eends%20up%20frustrated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20my%20daughter%20storms%20off%20to%20her%20room.%20It's%20the%20same%20conclusion%20every%20time.%20She%20feels%20judged%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20give%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20and%20I%20have%20always%20been%20very%20close%20since%20the%20day%20she%20was%20born%2C%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-support-teens-from-a-mom-who-raised-five-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteen%20years%20tested%20us%20both%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20lose%20her%20because%20of%20our%20egos%20or%20because%20she%20would%20grow%20up%20and%20never%20talk%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20I%20realized%20I%20had%20set%20up%20%26quot%3BMommy%20and%20me%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhaving-twins-created-more-equity-in-parenting-with-my-partner-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edates%20with%20my%20twins%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20each%20one%20alone%20with%20me%20because%20sometimes%20we%20forget%20that%20twins%20have%20separate%20characters%20with%20different%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20never%20prioritized%20doing%20that%20with%20my%20teen%20daughter%3B%20maybe%20I%20just%20felt%20she%20was%20older%20now%20and%20didn't%20require%20my%20help%20as%20much%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20she%20needs%20me%20now%20even%20more%20as%20she's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychologist-parenting-teens-reminder-struggles-of-age-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enavigating%20these%20strange%20and%20difficult%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bdbb795e-05d3-4d03-a470-9db0b3fc1ebe%5C%22%3EWe%20have%20monthly%20dates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20scheduling%20monthly%20dates%20with%20her%2C%20just%20the%20two%20of%20us.%20We%20started%20going%20on%20short%20drives%20and%20stopping%20at%20a%20coffee%20shop%2C%20where%20we'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthree-questions-that-get-teenagers-to-talk-to-me-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esit%20and%20talk%20about%20random%20things%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20an%20hour%20or%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlowly%2C%20I%20felt%20our%20conversations%20change%3B%20her%20tone%20and%20demeanor%20even%20changed.%20I%20did%20my%20best%20not%20to%20make%20her%20feel%20judged%20or%20trapped.%20It%20was%20mainly%20a%20time%20to%20get%20closer%20to%20each%20other%20while%20working%20on%20our%20differences%20and%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20became%20more%20relaxed%20on%20those%20dates%2C%20we%20started%20spending%20longer%20periods%20of%20time%20together.%20I'd%20schedule%20a%20whole%20day%20of%20shopping%2C%20eating%2C%20and%20then%20going%20on%20a%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20we%20discussed%20really%20heavy%20and%20difficult%20conversations%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20listen%20to%20her%20better%2C%20and%20she%20reciprocated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be7e2449-7703-4c21-b9f4-75090965a331%5C%22%3EWe%20were%20both%20vulnerable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20helped%20us%20both%20was%20my%20being%20comfortable%20talking%20with%20her%20about%20my%20emotions%20and%20showing%20vulnerabilities%2C%20which%20I%20struggled%20with%20a%20lot%2C%20mainly%20in%20my%20life%20and%20as%20a%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20afraid%20that%20by%20sharing%20any%20vulnerability%20I%20have%20or%20fear%20or%20worry%2C%20I%20might%20cause%20more%20harm%2C%20mentally%20and%20emotionally%2C%20to%20her.%20But%20this%20fear%20stopped%20me%20from%20having%20many%20meaningful%20conversations%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20me%20that%20she%20feels%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20as%20the%20oldest%20child%20and%20that%20she%20always%20feels%20she%20needs%20to%20be%20perfect.%20I%20told%20her%20I%20feel%20a%20lot%20of%20burden%20placed%20on%20me%20as%20a%20mom%2C%20too%2C%20to%20do%20everything%20right%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20butting%20heads%20because%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20we%20both%20felt%20the%20same%20need%20and%20emotions%2C%20but%20our%20egos%20or%20fears%20stopped%20us%20from%20opening%20up%20about%20it.%20We%20needed%20to%20be%20outside%20a%20neutral%20zone%20to%20understand%20how%20similar%20we%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20experiment%20with%20my%20daughter%20taught%20me%20never%20to%20keep%20my%20feelings%20sealed%20because%20there's%20a%20lot%20at%20stake%20if%20you%20don't%20communicate.%20I'm%20not%20stopping%20our%20dates%20anytime%20soon%20because%20we%20are%20both%20getting%20a%20lot%20from%20them.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-takes-teen-on-dates-to-reconnect-have-relationship-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743207661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67e2c90fb8b41a9673fba0da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-takes-teen-on-dates-to-reconnect-have-relationship-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20mom%20of%20three%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20often%20overwhelmed%20at%20home.%20Taking%20my%20teen%20out%20for%20time%20alone%20together%20has%20helped%20us%20have%20a%20better%20relationship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Karen%20Habashi%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-takes-teen-on-dates-to-reconnect-have-relationship-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20did%20Donald%20Trump%20pull%20Elise%20Stefanik's%20UN%20nomination%3F%20Here's%20the%20answer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%2