als%20and%20allow%20them%20a%20fresh%20start.%20While%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%2C%20through%20diplomacy%20and%20its%20network%20of%20embassies%20and%20consulates%2C%20has%20helped%20secure%20the%20release%20of%20many%20such%20individuals%2C%20some%20tougher%20negotiations%20has%20seen%20a%20direct%20involvement%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20who%2C%20over%20his%20three%20terms%20so%20far%2C%20has%20build%20on%20a%20rapport%20with%20global%20leaders%20far%20and%20wide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20freedom%20of%20nearly%2010%2C000%20Indian%20nationals%20have%20been%20secured%20so%20far%20since%202014%2C%20a%20release%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20has%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20latest%20instance%20is%20the%20pardon%20of%20500%20Indian%20prisoners%20in%20UAE%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20foreign%20ministry%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BIt%20reflects%20the%20strong%20bilateral%20ties%20between%20India%20and%20UAE%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%202014%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20has%20prioritised%20the%20welfare%20of%20Indian%20citizens%20abroad%2C%20ensuring%20the%20safe%20return%20of%20nearly%2010%2C000%20Indian%20nationals%20imprisoned%20abroad%20through%20diplomatic%20negotiations%20and%20high-level%20interventions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20highlighted%20some%20key%20instances%20where%20several%20countries%20agreed%20to%20release%20or%20pardon%20Indian%20nationals%20due%20to%20diplomatic%20efforts%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EUNITED%20ARAB%20EMIRATES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20Between%202022%20and%202025%2C%20each%20year%20UAE%20has%20pardoned%20hundreds%20of%20Indian%20prisoners%2C%20including%20some%20during%20the%20holy%20month%20of%20Ramzan%20or%20the%20festival%20of%20Eid.%20In%202022%2C%20UAE%20released%20639%C2%A0%20Indian%20prisoners.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20count%20went%20beyond%20700.%20In%202024%20944%2C%20and%20in%202025%2C%20it%20has%20been%20500%20so%20far.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESAUDI%20ARABIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20In%202019%2C%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20India%2C%20Saudi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20had%20ordered%20the%20release%20of%20850%20Indian%20prisoners.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EQATAR%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20In%20a%20big%20diplomatic%20victory%20for%20New%20Delhi%2C%20after%20much%20negotiations%2C%20including%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%2C%20Qatar%20agreed%20to%20the%20release%20of%208%20Indian%20Navy%20veterans%20who%20were%20facing%20a%20death%20penalty.%20Most%20of%20them%20were%20subsequently%20allowed%20to%20return%20to%20India.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIRAN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20In%202023%20and%202024%2C%20Iran%20released%2043%20and%2077%20Indian%20nationals%20respectively%20from%20its%20jails.%20In%202023%2C%20out%20of%20the%2043%2C%2012%20were%20fishermen.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EBAHRAIN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20As%20a%20gesture%20of%20friendship%20and%20kindness%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20Bahrain%20decided%20to%20release%20250%20Indians%20who%20were%20in%20prison%20in%202019.%20They%20were%20freed%20during%20PM%20Modi's%20visit%20to%20the%20country%20that%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EKUWAIT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20In%202017%2C%20after%20several%20rounds%20of%20talks%20via%20diplomatic%20channels%2C%20the%20Emir%20of%20Kuwait%20agreed%20to%20release%2022%20Indian%20nationals%20and%20reduce%20the%20sentences%20for%2097%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESRI%20LANKA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20-%20After%20regular%20interventions%20and%20mediation%20via%20diplomatic%20channels%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20has%2C%20on%20many%20occasions%2C%20released%20Indian%20fishermen%20who%20accidentally%20and%20unknowingly%20cross%20into%20its%20territorial%20waters.%20Since%202014%2C%20a%20total%20of%203%2C697%20Indian%20fishermen%20have%20been%20released%20by%20Sri%20Lanka.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPAKISTAN%3C%2Fstrong%3E