ed%22%3A1743180623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcricket%2Fipl%2Fkkr-vs-lsg-ipl-2025-match-rescheduled-in-april-due-to-security-reasons-125032801409_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20date%20change%20was%20made%20following%20requests%20from%20the%20Kolkata%20Police%20and%20the%20Cricket%20Association%20of%20Bengal%2C%20who%20cited%20a%20shortage%20of%20police%20personnel%20due%20to%20Ram%20navami%20festivities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20Says%20Russia%20Won't%20Interfere%20In%20Trump's%20Plan%20To%20Take%20Over%20Greenland%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Arctic%20is%20heating%20up%2C%20not%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20Climate%20Change%2C%20but%20also%20in%20terms%20of%20geopolitics.%20With%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20pressing%20to%20annex%20Greenland%20and%20Canada%2C%20Russia%20isn't%20to%20be%20left%20behind.%20President%20Putin%20today%20visited%20Murmansk%20-%20the%20largest%20city%20north%20of%20the%20Arctic%20circle%20where%20he%20pledged%20to%20%26quot%3Bstrengthen%20Russia's%20global%20leadership%20in%20the%20Arctic%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20President%20however%2C%20did%20not%20make%20any%20territorial%20claims%2C%20nor%20spoke%20of%20expansionism.%20What%20came%20as%20a%20surprise%20though%2C%20was%20President%20Putin's%20no-objection%20to%20President%20Trump's%20plan%20to%20annex%20Greenland%20and%20make%20it%20a%20US%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGeopolitical%20competition%20in%20the%20Arctic%20region%20is%20intensifying%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Putin%20said%2C%20giving%20Donald%20Trump's%20plan%20to%20take%20over%20Greenland%20as%20a%20primary%20example%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20significant%20shift%20in%20US%20foreign%20policy%2C%20President%20Putin%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAmerica's%20plans%20in%20relation%20to%20Greenland%20are%20serious.%20These%20plans%20have%20deep%20historical%20roots.%20And%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20US%20will%20continue%20to%20systematically%20pursue%20its%20geo-strategic%2C%20military%2C%20political%2C%20and%20economic%20interests%20in%20the%20Arctic%20region.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPUTIN'S%20NOD%20TO%20TRUMP%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20instead%20of%20criticizing%20or%20condemning%20Trump's%20expansionist%20agenda%2C%20Putin%20left%20Greenland%20to%20its%20fate.%20%26quot%3BAs%20for%20Greenland%20this%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20two%20specific%20countries%20(US%20and%20Denmark).%20It%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Putin%20said%C2%A0at%20Russia's%20Arctic%20Forum%20in%20Murmansk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin's%20statement%2C%20distancing%20Moscow%20from%20the%20Greenland%20matter%20entirely%2C%20has%20raised%20eyebrows%20globally.%20Geopolitical%20and%20military%20experts%20read%20this%20as%20Moscow's%20go-ahead%20to%20Washington%20to%20pursue%20its%20plans.%20The%20timing%20of%20Putin's%20statement%20is%20also%20interesting%20as%20the%20Kremlin%20and%20the%20White%20House%20are%20putting%20efforts%20to%20foster%20closer%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20returning%20to%20office%20in%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20too%2C%20has%20completely%20changed%20Washington's%20outlook%20and%20stance%20towards%20Moscow%2C%20leaving%20Europe%2C%20especially%20Ukraine%2C%20in%20the%20lurch.%20Anxious%20and%20worried%2C%20leaders%20across%20Europe%20are%20frequently%20huddling%20up%20in%20France%2C%20frantically%20seeking%20an%20alternative%20to%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin's%20stand%20on%20US'%20intent%20to%20'takeover'%20of%20Greenland%20may%20have%20repercussions%20for%20Ukraine%20too%2C%20where%20Russia%20has%20gained%20control%20of%20vast%20swathes%20of%20Ukrainian%20territory%2C%20which%20Moscow%20has%20no%20plans%20to%20returning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMOSCOW%20AND%20WASHINGTON%20-%20FOES-TURNED-FRIENDS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFar%20from%20criticizing%20each%20other%2C%20which%20was%20the%20norm%20till%20January%20this%20year%2C%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%20are%20now%20increasingly%20soft%20on%20each%20other%2C%20sometimes%20even%20agreeing%20on%20certain%20matters%20-%20like%20President%20Zelensky's%20behaviour%2C%20which%20Trump%20and%20his%20deputy%20JD%20Vance%20have%20severely%20criticized%20since%20the%20very-public%20showdown%20at%20the%20White%20House.%20Russian%20leaders%20echoing%20the%20US%20leadership's%20sentiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20President%20Putin's%20visit%20to%20the%20Arctic%20today%2C%20Moscow%20is%20promoting%20the%20idea%20that%20Russia%20and%20the%20US%20can%20cooperate%20in%20the%20region%2C%20which%20is%20rich%20in%20mineral%20and%20natural%20resources%2C%20as%20well%20as%20rare%20earth%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Putin's%20special%20envoy%20for%20foreign%20investment%20and%20economic%20cooperation%2C%20Kirill%20Dmitriev%2C%20said%20today%20that%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20open%20to%20considering%20different%20investment%20opportunities%20that%20we%20can%20do%20jointly%20with%20the%20US%2C%20in%20certain%20sectors%20approved%20by%20the%20Russian%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20open%20for%20investment%20cooperation%20in%20the%20Arctic.%20That%20could%20be%20in%20logistics%2C%20or%20other%20areas%20beneficial%20to%20Russia%20and%20to%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bbefore%20such%20deals%20can%20be%20done%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20needs%20to%20end.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20(Russia%20and%20the%20US)%20now%20have%20a%20very%20good%20dialogue%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20is%20very%20important%20that%20the%20US%20is%20trying%20to%20understand%20Russia's%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Dmitriev%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%