B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20today%20appraised%20Parliament%20about%20the%20rising%20incidents%20of%20attacks%20on%20minorities%20in%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh.%20The%20minister%20cited%20ten%20major%20incidents%20involving%20brutal%20attacks%20on%20Hindus%20in%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20month%20of%20February%20alone%2C%20while%20updating%20MPs%20about%20the%20atrocities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNew%20Delhi%20tracks%20the%20treatment%20of%20minorities%20in%20Pakistan%20very%20closely%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20has%20made%20its%20position%20regarding%20action%20on%20Pakistan%20%26quot%3Bwell%20known%26quot%3B.%20During%20his%20address%20to%20parliamentarians%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20highlighted%20Pakistan's%20%26quot%3Bfanatical%20and%20bigoted%20mindset%26quot%3B%20towards%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20ten%20gruesome%20incidents%20he%20mentioned%2C%20seven%20of%20them%20were%20related%20to%20abductions%2C%20disappearances%2C%20and%20forced%20conversions%20to%20Islam%2C%20two%20others%20were%20about%20kidnappings%2C%20and%20one%20even%20involved%20police%20brutality%20on%20students%20for%20merely%20celebrating%20Holi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20Hindus%2C%20but%20Sikhs%20were%20targeted%20to%2C%20the%20minister%20said.%20He%20narrated%20three%20incidents%20related%20to%20atrocities%20against%20members%20of%20the%20Sikh%20community.%20In%20one%20instance%2C%20a%20family%20of%20Sikhs%20were%20attacked%20and%20brutalised%20allegedly%20for%20resisting%20forced%20conversion.%20In%20the%20second%20case%2C%20another%20family%20of%20Sikhs%20faced%20death%20threats%20for%20reopening%20an%20old%20Gurdwara%20and%20practicing%20their%20faith.%20The%20third%20incident%20was%20about%20a%20Sikh%20girl%20being%20abducted%20and%20kept%20in%20captivity.%20She%20was%20allegedly%20tortured%20till%20she%20agreed%20to%20convert%20to%20Islam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20Muslims%20from%20the%20Ahmediya%20community%2C%20who%20are%20not%20considered%20Muslims%20be%20extremists%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20were%20targeted%2C%20as%20was%20a%20Christian%20person%20of%20unsound%20mind%2C%20who%20was%20charged%20by%20the%20state%20for%20%26quot%3Bblasphemy%26quot%3B.%20These%20are%20just%20a%20few%20examples%20of%20attacks%20on%20minorities%20only%20in%20the%20month%20of%20February%2C%20said%20the%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Bangladesh%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLike%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20we%20track%20the%20welfare%20and%20well-being%20of%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh%20as%20well.%20In%202024%2C%20we%20had%202%2C400%20incidents%20relating%20to%20attacks%20on%20minorities%20and%20in%202025%2C%2072%20incidents.%20I%20have%20taken%20it%20up%20with%20my%20counterpart%20there.%20The%20foreign%20secretary%20also%20took%20it%20up%20when%20he%20visited%20Bangladesh.%20This%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20for%20our%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20these%2C%20there%20are%20reports%20of%20thousands%20of%20cases%20of%20atrocities%2C%20abductions%2C%20forced%20disappearances%2C%20torture%2C%20and%20killings%20in%20Balochistan%20-%20a%20region%20where%20Pakistan%20is%20infamous%20for%20its%20gross%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20India%20plans%20any%20%26quot%3Btough%20action%26quot%3B%20against%20Pakistan%20-%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20what%20former%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20done%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNew%20Delhi's%20position%20is%20well%20known%26quot%3B.%20He%20however%20said%20that%20despite%20the%20steps%20India%20takes%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20as%20a%20government%20and%20a%20country%20cannot%20change%20the%20fanatical%20and%20bigoted%20mindset%20of%20our%20neighbour.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20%26quot%3BEven%20Indira%20Gandhi%20could%20not%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20implying%20that%20despite%20losing%20East%20Pakistan%